block prepend vars
  -var appName = 'Contact App'

doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    title #{appName}
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='styles/main.css')

    //- Uncomment one of the lines below to pull in either your app JS, or some library JS.
    //- script(src='/scripts/app/main.js') //- A single page application script.
    //- script(src='/scripts/lib/demoLib.js') //- A project built lib script.
    //- script(src='/lib/foo/bar.min.js') //- A bower installed script.

  body
    h1 #{appName}

    h2 Because contact forms needn't be hard work

    ol
      li Copy/paste our snippet into your web page
      li Start receiving messages at your designated email address

    h2 A designer's best friend

    ul
      li Add additional fields and validations <b>without code</b>.
      li Integrate 100% seamlessly with your pages, no awkward styling.
      li Client and server-side validation right out of the box.
      li Performs flawlessly on all devices.

    h2 No sign-up

    p We'll contact you on your nominated email address if we need anything.


    p Demo script for mike to dev with, no validation, sends to mike@mcarter.me

    form(id='leaf-hello')
      label Name:
      input(type='text', name='name')
      br
      label Email:
      input(type='text', name='email')
      br
      label Message:
      br
      textarea(name='message', rows='10', cols='100')
      br
      input(type='submit', value='Send it')
    script(src='/scripts/app/contactFormHandler.app.js')